description:
More than ten years ago, I dared to imagine the first French fashion brand to be born online... Les Composantes, which has since become Sézane. My priorities haven't changed since then: to innovate and to put people, creativity, quality, respect and service at the heart of everything we do.

To continue to co-construct the next chapter and beyond, we are looking for creative, organized and agile talents, who share our passion to perpetually improve all that can be.

Sézane is a playground which resembles no other, your job today won't be the same as yesterday, and probably nothing like tomorrow. If that appeals to you, we can't wait to hear from you!

We are seeking the talents of a Logistics Project Manager (M/F) to contribute to the next chapter of Sézane's journey. You will contribute to performance improvement (costs, quality, lead times, CSR) of Logistics Operations at our new Hanover Logistics hub. The position is based in Hanover, Germany.

Your Missions Will Be The Following


 * Conduct an assessment of the current situation (audits, diagnostics)
 * Ensure competitive and technological monitoring;
 * Identify and analyze needs, prioritizing them based on customer impact, ROI, and complexity;
 * Create a functional specification document (context, objectives, stakeholders, budget, deadlines, competitive analysis, etc.);
 * Prepare the project by creating a roadmap that includes key dates for the various project phases;
 * Plan actions and coordinate the different stakeholders to ensure deadlines and objectives are met;
 * Provide regular reporting to Logistics Director and COO throughout the project;
 * Oversee the transition to the operational phase of the project: organize testing phases;
 * Train future users;
 * Ensure that the project meets expectations (deadlines, costs, results post-operational implementation);
 * Keeping all the associated documentation updated in a timely manner;
 * Additionally, you will act as the on-site liaison for the Europe Logistics Director (based in Paris), tasked with overseeing the contractual logistics service (costs, quality, deadlines).



Requirements


 * With a Master's degree (Bac+5) from a General Engineering School, you have a minimum of 3 - 5 years of experience in an operational role and/or as a project manager in supply chain/logistics topics;
 * Rigor, attention to detail, pragmatism, autonomy, and strong interpersonal skills are key to your success;
 * Fluency in English and German is required, French language skills are a definite plus.



Sézane recruits and values all talents, whatever your gender, age, nationality, culture, religious beliefs or sexual orientation. If this role and Sézane speaks to you, apply now !
